{"status":"ok","count":4,"count_total":4,"pages":1,"posts":[{"id":146,"type":"post","slug":"r-i-p-ruby-on-rails-thanks-for-everything","url":"http:\/\/alesanchezr.com\/blog\/r-i-p-ruby-on-rails-thanks-for-everything\/","status":"publish","title":"R.I.P. Ruby on Rails. Thanks for everything.","title_plain":"R.I.P. Ruby on Rails. Thanks for everything.","content":"<p>I don&#8217;t mean to troll Ruby fans, but\u00a0let&#8217;s be objectives here. Rails framework gave us a lot, it changed the way\u00a0web products were made, but\u00a0now the most used languages have copycats, who needs Ruby? Ruby is so 2007..<\/p>\n<p><strong>PHP<\/strong><\/p>\n<p><img class=\"center aligncenter\" src=\"https:\/\/media.licdn.com\/mpr\/mpr\/shrinknp_400_400\/AAEAAQAAAAAAAASIAAAAJGQyOWQ0NDRkLTZjODktNDVjMC1iN2FmLWNhYjVlNWIyMmM5ZA.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"295\" height=\"179\" data-loading-tracked=\"true\" \/><\/p>\n<p>PHP Has proven to be a great survivor: 82% of the web\u00a0uses PHP. WordPress is 25% by itself. Is the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.google.ca\/trends\/explore#q=%2Fm%2F060kv%2C%20%2Fm%2F0bbxf89%2C%20%2Fm%2F07sbkfb%2C%20%2Fm%2F06ff5&amp;date=today%2012-m&amp;cmpt=q&amp;tz=Etc%2FGMT%2B5\" target=\"_blank\">second language with most interest in google<\/a>. In <a href=\"http:\/\/stackoverflow.com\/research\/developer-survey-2015\" target=\"_blank\">stack-overflow 2015 developer survey<\/a>, PHP was the most popular\u00a0language between PHP, Ruby, Nodejs and Python. And was the second language with most questions. PHP Frameworks are phenomenal:\u00a0<a href=\"https:\/\/laravel.com\/\" target=\"_blank\">Laravel<\/a>,\u00a0<a href=\"https:\/\/phpixie.com\/\" target=\"_blank\">Phpixie<\/a>, etc.<\/p>\n<figure style=\"width: 600px;\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img class=\"center\" src=\"https:\/\/media.licdn.com\/mpr\/mpr\/shrinknp_800_800\/AAEAAQAAAAAAAAbcAAAAJDgxNmVkZmFhLTJkMTMtNDVlNS1hODgzLWNmZDRiNzM3MGJhYg.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"300\" data-loading-tracked=\"true\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-caption-text\">Stack Overflow Questions on PHP<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p><strong>Java<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>Java is the most used language by far, specially because\u00a0is the language for the enterprises, almost every financial institution use it, also: Gmail, eBay, Amazon, insurance applications, etc. The largest applications vendors (like SAP) use it. Java is going to keep strong for a lot of time, maybe forever.<\/p>\n<p><strong>Python<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>Python is a very mature language;\u00a0you can do almost whatever you want with it. And it will never die. A lot\u00a0of websites are made in Python: Google, Youtube, Dropbox, Quora, Yahoo, Pinterest, Instagram, Spotify, etc. <a href=\"https:\/\/www.shoop.io\/en\/blog\/25-of-the-most-popular-python-and-django-websites\/\" target=\"_blank\">Check the full list here.<\/a><\/p>\n<p><strong>Javascript (JS)<\/strong><\/p>\n<p><img class=\"left alignleft\" src=\"https:\/\/media.licdn.com\/mpr\/mpr\/shrinknp_200_200\/AAEAAQAAAAAAAAPzAAAAJDM1ZWVkYjA3LTVhYTItNDkzYi1iMWJiLTdhZmU2ODYwOTg1OQ.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"151\" height=\"140\" data-loading-tracked=\"true\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Oh my, where do I start? You need to learn Javascript now! JS and Node are rising strong. It is the most popular technology in the world, the most used language on the web (almost every website needs a bit of Javascript), it&#8217;s the native language of web browsers! NodeJS is the framework with most job vacancies on indeed.com (for example). The only problem with JS are the frameworks, they are changing a lot and developers need to be constantly upgrading or redoing all the code, maybe in 2016 that will change, but it does not matter, because the future of Javascript is the brightest of all!<\/p>\n","excerpt":"<p class=\"excerpt\">I don&#8217;t mean to troll Ruby fans, but\u00a0let&#8217;s be objectives here. Rails framework gave us a lot, it changed the way\u00a0web products were made, but\u00a0now the most used languages have copycats, who needs Ruby? Ruby is so 2007.. PHP PHP Has proven to be a great survivor: 82% of the web\u00a0uses PHP. WordPress is 25% by itself. Is the second &#8230; <a class=\"read-more\" href=\"http:\/\/alesanchezr.com\/blog\/r-i-p-ruby-on-rails-thanks-for-everything\/\">Read More<\/a><\/p>\n","date":"2016-02-01 02:14:11","modified":"2016-02-02 04:10:31","categories":[],"tags":[{"id":25,"slug":"programming","title":"programming","description":"","post_count":1},{"id":26,"slug":"software-development","title":"software development","description":"","post_count":1}],"author":{"id":1,"slug":"alesanchezr","name":"alesanchezr","first_name":"","last_name":"","nickname":"alesanchezr","url":"","description":""},"comments":[],"attachments":[],"comment_count":0,"comment_status":"open","custom_fields":{"original-source-url":["https:\/\/www.linkedin.com\/pulse\/rip-ruby-rails-thanks-everything-alejandro-s%C3%A1nchez"]}},{"id":135,"type":"post","slug":"the-fraud-behind-the-c-a-of-digital-certificates","url":"http:\/\/alesanchezr.com\/blog\/the-fraud-behind-the-c-a-of-digital-certificates\/","status":"publish","title":"The fraud behind the C.A. of digital certificates is over","title_plain":"The fraud behind the C.A. of digital certificates is over","content":"<p>Internet does not escape to the same concept of &#8220;organized mafias&#8221; that occur in the real world. Companies certificate authorities\u00a0operate just like any other big enterprise,\u00a0with a fake &#8220;freedom of economy&#8221; \u00a0behind a oligopoly that kills all competitors and with a very expensive product that don&#8217;t generate any reasonable value.<\/p>\n<h3><strong>What is the objective behind a certification authority?<\/strong><\/h3>\n<p>The are supposed to be something like the &#8220;internet police&#8221;, making sure that\u00a0websites that handle sensible information meet the requirements to do so.<\/p>\n<h3><strong>Have you ever tried to implement a SSL Certificate?<\/strong><\/h3>\n<p>Is\u00a0not a hard process, pretty standard,\u00a0you have to do everything yourself using the same open source tools and techniques that everybody uses, then&#8230; when everything is done,\u00a0you pay a lot of money to the &#8220;Certificate authority&#8221;\u00a0and they give their permission to publish your website. If you don&#8217;t ask for their\u00a0permission the internet browsers will block your site with a gigantic proportions sign that says that hackers may be trying to get your information.<\/p>\n<figure id=\"attachment_137\" style=\"width: 419px;\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><a href=\"http:\/\/alesanchezr.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/01\/cert.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-137\" src=\"http:\/\/alesanchezr.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/01\/cert-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"cert\" width=\"419\" height=\"314\" \/><\/a><figcaption class=\"wp-caption-text\">Even google has been a victim of having the SSL certificate not verified.<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>What\u00a0this Certificate Authorities offer?<\/strong><\/h3>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">I remember the first time I needed to buy one I was very confused, I did not believe that the\u00a0differences between each certificate were\u00a0about what color the URL bar turns into, the color of the &#8220;Lock&#8221; icon, how many years the certificate longs and how many domains or subdomains can use it. <a href=\"https:\/\/www.digicert.com\/ssl-certificate-comparison.htm\">Enter here and you will see for your self.<\/a><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-138 alignleft\" src=\"http:\/\/alesanchezr.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/01\/browser-greenbar-300x85.jpg\" alt=\"browser-greenbar\" width=\"300\" height=\"85\" \/>After reading a lot, I\u00a0understood\u00a0that it was all about the green bar, that&#8217;s it. You can have the strongest encrypted and safest\u00a0website in the world but if you\u00a0don&#8217;t have the green bar, you are\u00a0screwed because people think that you are\u00a0less secure than the others.<\/p>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>But how much\u00a0does the green bar costs?<\/strong><\/h3>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">After 30 minutes browsing different options my average price is 200 dollars!! They don&#8217;t even do real background checks of the companies to which they provide the certificate, you could be using the website to do some phishing or any other bad thing. The only thing the verify (if you pay enough) is the address.<\/p>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">The light at the end of the tunnel<\/h3>\n<figure id=\"attachment_139\" style=\"width: 166px;\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img class=\"wp-image-139\" src=\"http:\/\/alesanchezr.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/01\/Screen-Shot-2016-01-26-at-10.05.44-PM-275x300.png\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2016-01-26 at 10.05.44 PM\" width=\"166\" height=\"181\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-caption-text\">Let&#8217;s Encrypt sponsors<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">I&#8217;m writing this articule because today, thank&#8217;s to Eny Rueda (Chief Technology Officer of 4Geeks), I find\u00a0out\u00a0about <a href=\"https:\/\/letsencrypt.org\">Let&#8217;s Encrypt<\/a>\u00a0and I&#8217;m VERY happy about it.\u00a0They provide a free digital certificate for your site, but\u00a0the most impressive thing is that a great group of companies like Facebook, Mozilla, Google and Cisco\u00a0are\u00a0behind the project.<\/p>\n<blockquote>\n<h2><\/h2>\n<h2><\/h2>\n<h2>Let\u2019s\u00a0Encrypt is a new Certificate Authority:<br \/>\n<strong>It\u2019s free, automated, and open<\/strong>. <small><br \/>\nIn Public Beta<\/small><\/h2>\n<\/blockquote>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\"><\/h3>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">The Internet Security Research Group (ISRG)<\/h3>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Is a California public benefit corporation, and is recognized by the IRS as a tax-exempt organization under Section 501(c)(3) of the Internal Revenue Code. ISRG\u2019s mission is to reduce financial, technological, and education barriers to secure communication over the Internet.<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">It seems that good news are coming to the internet, and eventually we could\u00a0stop paying all that money to the Certification Authorities.<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">\n","excerpt":"<p class=\"excerpt\">Internet does not escape to the same concept of &#8220;organized mafias&#8221; that occur in the real world. Companies certificate authorities\u00a0operate just like any other big enterprise,\u00a0with a fake &#8220;freedom of economy&#8221; \u00a0behind a oligopoly that kills all competitors and with a very expensive product that don&#8217;t generate any reasonable value. What is the objective behind a certification authority? The are &#8230; <a class=\"read-more\" href=\"http:\/\/alesanchezr.com\/blog\/the-fraud-behind-the-c-a-of-digital-certificates\/\">Read More<\/a><\/p>\n","date":"2016-01-26 22:07:18","modified":"2016-02-01 02:19:17","categories":[],"tags":[],"author":{"id":1,"slug":"alesanchezr","name":"alesanchezr","first_name":"","last_name":"","nickname":"alesanchezr","url":"","description":""},"comments":[],"attachments":[{"id":137,"url":"http:\/\/alesanchezr.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/01\/cert.jpg","slug":"cert","title":"cert","description":"","caption":"","parent":135,"mime_type":"image\/jpeg","images":{"full":{"url":"http:\/\/alesanchezr.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/01\/cert.jpg","width":480,"height":360},"thumbnail":{"url":"http:\/\/alesanchezr.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/01\/cert-150x150.jpg","width":150,"height":150},"medium":{"url":"http:\/\/alesanchezr.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/01\/cert-300x225.jpg","width":300,"height":225},"large":{"url":"http:\/\/alesanchezr.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/01\/cert.jpg","width":480,"height":360}}},{"id":138,"url":"http:\/\/alesanchezr.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/01\/browser-greenbar.jpg","slug":"browser-greenbar","title":"browser-greenbar","description":"","caption":"","parent":135,"mime_type":"image\/jpeg","images":{"full":{"url":"http:\/\/alesanchezr.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/01\/browser-greenbar.jpg","width":510,"height":144},"thumbnail":{"url":"http:\/\/alesanchezr.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/01\/browser-greenbar-150x144.jpg","width":150,"height":144},"medium":{"url":"http:\/\/alesanchezr.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/01\/browser-greenbar-300x85.jpg","width":300,"height":85},"large":{"url":"http:\/\/alesanchezr.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/01\/browser-greenbar.jpg","width":510,"height":144}}},{"id":139,"url":"http:\/\/alesanchezr.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/01\/Screen-Shot-2016-01-26-at-10.05.44-PM.png","slug":"screen-shot-2016-01-26-at-10-05-44-pm","title":"Screen Shot 2016-01-26 at 10.05.44 PM","description":"","caption":"","parent":135,"mime_type":"image\/png","images":{"full":{"url":"http:\/\/alesanchezr.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/01\/Screen-Shot-2016-01-26-at-10.05.44-PM.png","width":872,"height":950},"thumbnail":{"url":"http:\/\/alesanchezr.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/01\/Screen-Shot-2016-01-26-at-10.05.44-PM-150x150.png","width":150,"height":150},"medium":{"url":"http:\/\/alesanchezr.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/01\/Screen-Shot-2016-01-26-at-10.05.44-PM-275x300.png","width":275,"height":300}}}],"comment_count":0,"comment_status":"open","custom_fields":{}},{"id":104,"type":"post","slug":"manteniendo-las-raices","url":"http:\/\/alesanchezr.com\/blog\/manteniendo-las-raices\/","status":"publish","title":"Manteniendo las raices","title_plain":"Manteniendo las raices","content":"<p>Hoy me volvi\u00f3 a pasar, cada vez que salgo a la calle -a pesar de que los a\u00f1os pasan- me doy cuenta de lo visionaria que fue nuestra propuesta de hace 4 a\u00f1os\u2026 Todo el mundo sufre el mismo problema, y cada vez ser\u00e1 peor, sobretodo en Latinoam\u00e9rica.<\/p>\n<p>Durante el \u00faltimo mes hemos presentado a 4Geeks en cientos de lugares y empresas Mexicanas, ustedes deber\u00edan estar conmigo en esas reuniones, ver la cara de la gente, como te miran, te ponen atenci\u00f3n, se identifican con la causa, \u00a0te quieren urgentemente, eres su salvador y aman tu propuesta.<\/p>\n<p>El mundo -y en especial Latinoam\u00e9rica- necesita a 4Geeks, necesita m\u00e1s y mejores desarrolladores, necesita aprovechar toda esa tecnolog\u00eda que hay disponible, y utilizarla para mejorar, optimizar, reinventar, producir\u2026 cambiar el mundo.<\/p>\n<p>\u00bfQu\u00e9 tiene 4Geeks de diferente al resto?\u00bfPor qu\u00e9 el mundo necesita a 4Geeks y no necesita m\u00e1s consultoras de software?<\/p>\n<p>Basta con escribir \u201cdesarrollo de p\u00e1ginas web\u201d en Google para darse cuenta de la gran cantidad de empresas que hoy en d\u00eda ofrecen este servicio, hacer una p\u00e1gina web no es innovar, eso es un<em>comodity<\/em>, la \u00fanica decisi\u00f3n de compra se debe al precio. Esa labor es mejor dej\u00e1rsela a las \u201cboutiques\u201d o a los freelancers que quieran \u201cmatar tigres\u201d para rebuscarse.<\/p>\n<p>Por otro lado tienes a las grandes consultoras de software, que hacen grandes implementaciones de SAP, o de IMB Websphere y otras miles de plataformas con miles de acr\u00f3nimos interminables; ellos est\u00e1n en su mundo cuadriculado, olvidaron como es el mundo real y el verdadero fin de \u201chacer software\u201d. Son v\u00edctimas del sistema en si mismo.<\/p>\n<p>Aqu\u00ed es cuando viene 4Geeks, a hacer software de verdad: \u00fatil, \u00e1gil, r\u00e1pido y sin burocracia. La labor de nosotros es crear un ejercito de S\u00faper Desarrolladores, hackers, y no dejar que se quemen en un mundo cuadriculado, ni que se quemen haciendo cosas banales. Que se utilicen, que se explote su verdadero potencial conect\u00e1ndolos con los grandes proyectos que logren grandes cosas.<\/p>\n<p>Hoy mas que nunca, me queda claro que nuestra misi\u00f3n y visi\u00f3n est\u00e1n bien encaminadas, seguiremos creciendo para hacer esta comunidad m\u00e1s grande, de s\u00faper desarrolladores, y enfocados en s\u00faper proyectos.<\/p>\n","excerpt":"<p class=\"excerpt\">Hoy me volvi\u00f3 a pasar, cada vez que salgo a la calle -a pesar de que los a\u00f1os pasan- me doy cuenta de lo visionaria que fue nuestra propuesta de hace 4 a\u00f1os\u2026 Todo el mundo sufre el mismo problema, y cada vez ser\u00e1 peor, sobretodo en Latinoam\u00e9rica. Durante el \u00faltimo mes hemos presentado a 4Geeks en cientos de lugares &#8230; <a class=\"read-more\" href=\"http:\/\/alesanchezr.com\/blog\/manteniendo-las-raices\/\">Read More<\/a><\/p>\n","date":"2015-12-02 02:07:46","modified":"2015-12-02 02:08:05","categories":[],"tags":[],"author":{"id":1,"slug":"alesanchezr","name":"alesanchezr","first_name":"","last_name":"","nickname":"alesanchezr","url":"","description":""},"comments":[],"attachments":[],"comment_count":0,"comment_status":"open","custom_fields":{}},{"id":47,"type":"post","slug":"df-tech-meetup-ya-es-una-realidad","url":"http:\/\/alesanchezr.com\/blog\/df-tech-meetup-ya-es-una-realidad\/","status":"publish","title":"DF Tech Meetup, ya es una realidad","title_plain":"DF Tech Meetup, ya es una realidad","content":"<p>Estoy muy feliz, luego de tantas vueltas hemos logrado dar con un lugar donde realmente conseguimos las condiciones necesarias para realizar el DF Tech Meetup como Dios manda. En anteriores espacios nos hab\u00edan dado una lista de exigencias y condiciones que no est\u00e1bamos dispuestos a aceptar (al menos eso dec\u00edamos) y por eso continu\u00e1bamos buscando.<\/p>\n<p>Pero al final vali\u00f3 la pena, gracias a nuestros nuevos amigos de Centraal, tenemos un lugar que ademas de ser incre\u00edble, no tiene condiciones, podemos poner nuestra propia publicidad, podemos hacer nuestra propia convocatoria, y hasta nos consiguieron patrocinio de GOOGLE. \u00bfC\u00f3mo les queda? Google va a ser sponsor del DF Tech Meetup.<\/p>\n<p>Ademas resulto que varios de los socios de Centraal son venezolanos, hicimos una buen\u00edsima sinergia, y hasta en Hack quieren colaborar o participar como les permitamos (buenas noticias, Romer). Vamos a ver como sale la cosa, ahora toca ponerse a planificar. El meetup es el 24 de Abril, vamos a ver si lo pasamos por streaming para que todo el mundo lo pueda ver.<\/p>\n<p>Todavia seguimos buscando patrocinantes para ver si financiamos el equipo organizador y logramos hacer que los DF Tech Meetups sean mensuales como en Venezuela, hay un candidato interesado, vamos a ver como sale la cosa, les estar\u00e9 contando.<\/p>\n","excerpt":"<p class=\"excerpt\">Estoy muy feliz, luego de tantas vueltas hemos logrado dar con un lugar donde realmente conseguimos las condiciones necesarias para realizar el DF Tech Meetup como Dios manda. En anteriores espacios nos hab\u00edan dado una lista de exigencias y condiciones que no est\u00e1bamos dispuestos a aceptar (al menos eso dec\u00edamos) y por eso continu\u00e1bamos buscando. Pero al final vali\u00f3 la &#8230; <a class=\"read-more\" href=\"http:\/\/alesanchezr.com\/blog\/df-tech-meetup-ya-es-una-realidad\/\">Read More<\/a><\/p>\n","date":"2015-12-01 18:22:05","modified":"2015-12-02 02:08:35","categories":[],"tags":[],"author":{"id":1,"slug":"alesanchezr","name":"alesanchezr","first_name":"","last_name":"","nickname":"alesanchezr","url":"","description":""},"comments":[],"attachments":[],"comment_count":0,"comment_status":"open","custom_fields":{}}]}